HEADWORD: Et cætera
<hw>Et` c⟦ae⟧t"e*ra</hw> }</mhw>
<pr>(?)</pr>. <ety>[L. <ets>et</ets> and + <ets>caetera</ets> other
things.]</ety> <def>Others of the like kind; and the rest; and so on; --
used to point out that <xex>other things</xex> which could be mentioned
are to be understood. Usually abbreviated into <it>etc.</it> or &c.
(<it>&c.</it>)</def> <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

